<section xml:id="section-assignment-week10">
  <title>Week 10 Assignment</title>
  <p><ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        Find the (real) eigenvalues and eigenvectors of these
        matrices. Feel free to use a computer for the row reductions
        and for the roots of the complicated polynomials, but make
        sure you clearly indicate all the steps in the process. (12)
      </p>
      <p><ol>
        <li><me>
          \begin{pmatrix}
            0 \amp -1 \amp -1 \\
            -1 \amp 0 \amp 5 \\
            -1 \amp 5 \amp 3 
          \end{pmatrix}
        </me></li>
        <li><me>
          \begin{pmatrix}
            -12 \amp -6 \amp -6 \\
            13 \amp 7 \amp 7 \\
            2 \amp 2 \amp 2 
          \end{pmatrix}
        </me></li>
      </ol></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        How much can you determine about the eigenvalues of these
        three types of matrices? (For each, try to see if you can
        exactly determine the eigenvalues from the definitions and
        properties. Otherwise, state what partial information can be
        concluded.) (9) 
      </p>
      <p><ol>
        <li>
          A matrix with determinant zero.
        </li>
        <li>
          An orthogonal matrix. 
        </li>
        <li>
          A special orthogonal matrix. 
        </li>
      </ol></p>
    </li>
  </ol></p>
</section>
